=======================================================================

The bones shader pack contains original GLSL implementations of many
well‑known computer graphics algorithms.  The following sections list
the research papers, open‑source projects, and public domain techniques
that inspired or are directly used by bones.  Where source code has been
adapted, the original license is reproduced below.  All modifications
made for the bones project are released under the GPL‑3.0‑or‑later
license stated above; the algorithm descriptions and original works
remain the intellectual property of their respective authors.

Sections below follow the runtime effect order: geometric, denoise,
anti‑aliasing, sharpening / local contrast, blur, image quality,
temporal processing, exposure, tonemapping, white balance, colour
grading, channel curves, colour balance, selective colour,
stylization, accessibility, inline effects, hardware simulation,
overlay.

=======================================================================
GEOMETRIC (UV WARP)
=======================================================================

polynomial_distort / barrel_undistort
  Based on the Brown‑Conrady radial lens distortion model
  (widely used in OpenCV camera calibration). bones uses a
  single‑term (k1) approximation rather than the full k1/k2 polynomial.

fisheye_warp
  Employs an atan remapping to simulate a fisheye lens projection.

sharp_bilinear
  Pixel‑art upscaling using Hermite smoothstep UV snapping.
  Technique is a common shader idiom.

=======================================================================
DENOISE
=======================================================================

bilateral_denoise
  Spatial bilateral filter after Tomasi & Manduchi (1998),
  “Bilateral Filtering for Gray and Color Images”.

=======================================================================
ANTI‑ALIASING
=======================================================================

luma_edge_aa (FXAA)
  Based on “FXAA – Fast Approximate Anti‑Aliasing” by Timothy Lottes
  (NVIDIA).  The reference implementation is distributed under the
  permissive “FXAA 3.11” license (included below).

normal_filter_aa (NFAA)
  Normal Filter Anti‑Aliasing – computes gradient perpendicular to edges
  and blends along the tangent. Lightweight, public‑domain technique.

morphological_aa (CMAA)
  Inspired by Intel’s Conservative Morphological Anti‑Aliasing (CMAA).
  Original CMAA is distributed under the Apache License 2.0.

subpixel_aa (SMAA)
  Based on “SMAA: Enhanced Subpixel Morphological Antialiasing”
  by Jorge Jimenez, Jose I. Echevarria, Tiago Sousa, Diego Gutierrez
  (2012).  Reference implementation distributed under the MIT license.

=======================================================================
SHARPENING / LOCAL CONTRAST
=======================================================================

contrast_adaptive_sharpen (CAS)
  Derived from AMD FidelityFX CAS.
  Distributed under the MIT license (see below).

robust_contrast_sharpen (RCAS)
  Derived from AMD FidelityFX FSR 1.0 (RCAS).
  Distributed under the MIT license.

edge_directed_sharpen (NIS)
  Based on NVIDIA Image Scaling (NIS) edge‑aware sharpening.
  Distributed under the MIT license.

laplacian_sharpen
  Classic Laplacian sharpening kernel.

luminance_sharpen
  Luminance‑only sharpening, akin to Lightroom’s Lab‑space sharpening.

midtone_clarity
  Midtone local contrast enhancement inspired by Photoshop “Clarity”.

falloff_sharpen / power_curve_sharpen
  Adaptive sharpening with inverse falloff or power‑curve response.

unsharp_mask
  Traditional photographic unsharp mask using a weighted 3×3 kernel.

local_contrast
  Per‑pixel contrast based on luminance ratio to neighborhood average;
  similar to DaVinci Resolve’s local contrast.

=======================================================================
BLUR
=======================================================================

gaussian_blur / box_blur / bokeh_blur / tilt_shift_blur / radial_blur
  Standard convolution and sampling patterns. Public domain techniques.

=======================================================================
IMAGE QUALITY
=======================================================================

gradient_deband
  Sampling‑based debanding inspired by mpv’s deband filter.

threshold_bloom
  Bright pixel glow via threshold and neighbourhood accumulation.

ghost_flare
  Lens flare ghost simulation – sampling along the vector from screen
  centre to pixel.

=======================================================================
TEMPORAL PROCESSING
=======================================================================

neighborhood_clamp_aa (TAA clamp)
  Based on the temporal anti‑aliasing technique described in
  “High‑Quality Temporal Supersampling” by Brian Karis (SIGGRAPH 2014)
  and “Filmic SMAA” by Jorge Jimenez (GDC 2016).

motion_reject_denoise
  Motion‑gated accumulation: heavily blend static pixels, snap on motion.

motion_detect_blur
  Motion‑blur by blending toward history proportional to per‑pixel change.

constant_blend_smooth
  Simple 50/50 temporal blend.

shutter_angle_smooth
  Physical camera shutter simulation (180° shutter angle).

spline_interp_smooth
  Cubic Hermite temporal reconstruction with extrapolated control
  points. Related to the Catmull‑Rom family of cubic interpolants
  (E. Catmull and R. Rom, 1974, "A Class of Local Interpolating Splines").

variance_decay_smooth
  Exponential IIR filter with variance‑based decay.

dualrate_smooth
  Dual‑rate adaptive filter (high blend for still areas, low for edges).

luminance_gate_smooth
  Luminance‑adaptive blending – more smoothing in dark regions.

contrast_gate_smooth
  Contrast‑adaptive blending based on local contrast magnitude.

gradient_gate_smooth
  Edge‑aware temporal blending using Sobel‑like gradient.

sigma_clip_smooth
  Variance clipping: history clamped to mean ± sigma of 3×3 neighbourhood.
  Described by Salvi (2016) as the core of modern TAA.

mitchell_kernel_smooth
  Mitchell‑Netravali spatial reconstruction combined with temporal blend:
  Don P. Mitchell and Arun N. Netravali (1988), “Reconstruction Filters
  in Computer Graphics”.

ycocg_clip_smooth
  YCoCg colour‑space AABB clamp with confidence weighting.
  Derived from AMD GPUOpen temporal stabilisation samples.
  (MIT license)

bilateral_history_smooth
  Bilateral temporal filter comparing neighbourhood averages of current
  and history frames.

perceptual_chroma_smooth
  YCbCr temporal blend with higher blend weight on chroma,
  exploiting human vision’s lower chroma temporal resolution.

frequency_split_smooth
  Decompose into low/high frequency bands with separate blend weights.

horn_schunck_smooth
  Implements the Horn‑Schunck optical flow algorithm:
  B. K. P. Horn and B. G. Schunck (1981), “Determining Optical Flow”.

convergent_accumulate
  Convergent temporal supersampling – gradually increases blend weight
  as pixel stability increases, inspired by DLSS temporal accumulation.

dualwarp_flow_smooth
  Dual‑warp frame interpolation with flow consistency checking.
  Inspired by AMD FidelityFX Frame Interpolation (part of FSR 3).
  (MIT license)

variance_flow_accumulate
  Motion‑compensated temporal accumulation with variance clipping and
  triple confidence gating. Based on the temporal supersampling papers
  by Brian Karis (SIGGRAPH 2014) and Jorge Jimenez (GDC 2016).

edge_reconstruct_smooth
  Edge‑directed temporal reconstruction with directional spatial
  reconstruction along edges, inspired by Intel XeSS DP4a fallback path.
  Original XeSS is under the Intel Simplified Software License
  (BSD‑like); bones uses only the described algorithm.

convergent_detail_recovery (automatic)
  Fused temporal stabilizer combining a motion gate that softens
  history influence on large per‑pixel changes (a lightweight
  disocclusion guard) with a pull toward the converged history
  representation. Implemented as a single block that activates
  automatically whenever any temporal mode is enabled.

=======================================================================
EXPOSURE
=======================================================================

linear_exposure
  Fixed multiplier applied before tonemapping.

=======================================================================
TONEMAPPING
=======================================================================

aces_tonemap
  Algebraic fit by Krzysztof Narkowicz (2015) of the ACES
  (Academy Color Encoding System) filmic curve.
  ACES is developed by the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences.

agx_tonemap
  AgX sigmoid tone mapper created by Troy Sobotka for Blender.
  Blender’s AgX implementation is released under the GNU GPL.

reinhard_tonemap
  Reinhard et al. (2002), “Photographic Tone Reproduction for
  Digital Images”.

hable_tonemap
  John Hable (2010), “Uncharted 2: HDR Lighting”, GDC 2010.
  Constants from the public presentation.

lottes_tonemap
  Timothy Lottes (2016), “Advanced Techniques and Optimization
  of HDR Color Pipelines”.

uchimura_tonemap
  Hajime Uchimura (2017), CEDEC 2017, Gran Turismo tone mapping.
  Constants from the public presentation.

tony_tonemap (Tony McMapface)
  Simple offset‑scale highlight rolloff.

khronos_tonemap
  Khronos Group PBR Neutral tone mapper, specified in the
  glTF 2.0 specification.

=======================================================================
WHITE BALANCE
=======================================================================

neutral_white_balance
  Chromatic adaptation to CIE D65 white point (sRGB / Rec.709 standard).

warm_temperature / cool_temperature
  Simple channel multipliers for warm or cool colour shift.

=======================================================================
COLOUR GRADING
=======================================================================

saturation_contrast_grade
  Combined saturation, contrast, and brightness adjustment.

levels_remap
  Input/output black‑white remapping as in Photoshop Levels.

gamma_correct
  Power‑law gamma adjustment.

vibrance_boost
  Smart saturation boost (Lightroom “Vibrance” algorithm).

hsl_transform
  Hue, saturation, lightness adjustment in HSL colour space.

split_tone
  Split‑toning with cool shadows and warm highlights (cinematic look).

lift_gamma_gain
  Three‑way colour corrector (lift, gamma, gain) as in DaVinci Resolve.

hermite_curves
  S‑curve contrast via Hermite smoothstep.

=======================================================================
CHANNEL CURVES
=======================================================================

red_channel_curve / green_channel_curve / blue_channel_curve
  Per‑channel Hermite S‑curve for fine colour control.

=======================================================================
COLOUR BALANCE
=======================================================================

trizone_color_balance
  Three‑zone (shadow, midtone, highlight) colour tint;
  same concept as DaVinci Resolve colour wheels.

=======================================================================
SELECTIVE COLOUR
=======================================================================

red_selective_saturate / green_selective_saturate / blue_selective_saturate
  Boost saturation of pixels whose dominant channel matches a specific colour.

=======================================================================
STYLIZATION
=======================================================================

dynamic_range_crush
  Clamp black and white points and re‑expand; “Instagram filter” look.

duotone_map
  Luminance‑driven blend between two colours (Spotify cover style).

color_wash_tint
  Subtle overall colour tint.

posterize_quantize
  Reduce colour levels (Photoshop Posterize).

bleach_bypass
  Desaturated high‑contrast look simulating bleach bypass film process
  (e.g., Saving Private Ryan). Uses overlay blend.

technicolor_process
  Vintage three‑strip Technicolor cross‑channel simulation.

midpoint_contrast
  Simple contrast boost by scaling distance from 0.5.

color_invert
  Photographic negative.

luminance_grayscale
  BT.709 luminance weights for perceptually correct grayscale.

=======================================================================
ACCESSIBILITY
=======================================================================

protanopia_simulation / deuteranopia_simulation / tritanopia_simulation
  Colour vision deficiency simulation using 3×3 transformation matrices.

protanopia_correct / deuteranopia_correct / tritanopia_correct
  Daltonization (correction) for red, green, or blue cone deficiencies.

=======================================================================
INLINE EFFECTS
=======================================================================

gaussian_grain
  Film grain using the Box‑Muller transform to generate Gaussian noise.

chromatic_aberration
  Lateral chromatic aberration by shifting red and blue channels.

red_halation
  Red halation glow – bright areas add red channel boost,
  simulating film halation.

anamorphic_streak
  Horizontal streak flare simulating anamorphic lens flare.

radial_vignette
  Radial darkened edges with smoothstep falloff.

cinematic_letterbox
  2.35:1 widescreen letterbox bars.

ordered_dither
  Bayer 4×4 ordered dither pattern (Bayer, 1973).

=======================================================================
HARDWARE SIMULATION
=======================================================================

--- Console GPU simulation ---

ps1_simulation
  PlayStation 1 GPU simulation. Coarse UV grid quantization to
  simulate GTE fixed‑point coordinate snapping, nearest‑neighbour
  sampling behaviour, 15‑bit colour with Bayer 4×4 ordered dithering.

saturn_simulation
  Sega Saturn GPU simulation. Coarse pixel quantization and
  luminance banding approximating gouraud shading interpolation,
  a dark desaturated palette with warm brown shift, and 15‑bit
  colour with dithering.

n64_simulation
  Nintendo 64 GPU simulation. UV grid quantization producing
  low‑resolution softness, radial distance fog, and a warm
  colour shift.

dreamcast_simulation
  Sega Dreamcast GPU simulation. Over‑bright colour response,
  boosted saturation, and a smoothstep specular boost on bright areas.

ps2_simulation
  PlayStation 2 GPU simulation. Pixel quantization, soft scanline
  modulation, and threshold bloom approximating GS overbright.

xbox_simulation
  Original Xbox GPU simulation. Highlight boost in bright regions,
  midtone lift simulating crude bloom, plastic specular feel,
  and a slight warm/green colour bias.

psp_simulation
  PlayStation Portable GPU simulation. UV phase quantization to
  480×272 native resolution, LCD gamma washout (black floor near
  6%, white ceiling near 92%), dark region banding via adaptive
  quantization, and slight desaturation.

ps3_simulation
  PlayStation 3 GPU simulation. Sub‑HD render quantization
  (about 72% native), crushed shadows from RSX gamma response,
  and a cool colour shift.

xbox360_simulation
  Xbox 360 GPU simulation. eDRAM tiling seam at one‑third and
  two‑thirds screen height, HDR gradient banding in bright regions
  (adaptive quantization steps), lifted warm gamma, slight
  desaturation, and a specular peak boost.

--- Display simulation ---

crt_simulation
  CRT TV simulation: barrel distortion in the geometric stage,
  RGB phosphor triad mask, scanline darkening, brightness
  compensation, and a low‑frequency brightness pulsing in the
  color stage. The pulsing replaces older time‑varying instability
  effects so temporal history stays aligned.

phosphor_amber / phosphor_green / phosphor_red
  Monochrome phosphor CRT emulation (amber, green, red).

scanline_darken
  Horizontal scanline darkening only.

oled_simulation
  OLED near‑black crush and saturation boost.

vhs_simulation
  VHS tape degradation: deterministic horizontal ripple in the
  geometric stage; per‑scanline tracking noise, full‑image luma
  noise, chroma desaturation, warm colour shift, and occasional
  dropout in the color stage.

lcd_subpixel
  Visible LCD subpixel grid overlay.

=======================================================================
OVERLAY
=======================================================================

fps_hud
  Seven‑segment FPS counter rendered as a signed distance field.

crosshair_overlay
  Centred neon crosshair with glow and centre dot.

